  <p>A wrapper function for <link xref="Gio.OutputStream.write"/> which takes a
<link xref="GLib.Bytes"/> as input.  This can be more convenient for use by language
bindings or in other cases where the refcounted nature of <link xref="GLib.Bytes"/>
is helpful over a bare pointer interface.</p>  <p>However, note that this function may still perform partial writes,
just like <link xref="Gio.OutputStream.write"/>.  If that occurs, to continue
writing, you will need to create a new <link xref="GLib.Bytes"/> containing just the
remaining bytes, using <link xref="GLib.new_from_bytes"/>. Passing the same
<link xref="GLib.Bytes"/> instance multiple times potentially can result in duplicated
data in the output stream.</p>

